class Solution {
public:
    long long minimumCost(string s) {
        int n = s.length();
        int cost[n + 1][2];
        for (int i = 0; i <= n; i++) {
            cost[i][0] = i;
            cost[i][1] = i;
        }
        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j <= n; j++) {
                if (s[j] == '0') {
                    cost[i][0] = min(cost[i][0], cost[i - s[j] - 1][0];
                } else {
                    cost[i][1] = min(cost[i][1], cost[i - s[j] - 1][1];
                }
            }
        }
        return cost[n][1];
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n^2)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW

Explanation:

We use a 2D array to store the minimum cost for each index i considering the characters before it (cost[i][0]) and considering the characters after it (cost[i][1]). We iterate through the string once to calculate the costs and return the minimum cost at the end.

The time complexity is O(n^2) because we have two nested loops, one for each dimension of the 2D array. The space complexity is O(n) because we use a 2D array with n rows and 2 columns. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs a single pass through the string and does not require any additional energy-consuming operations.

